The Department of Justice, under then-Attorney General Loretta Lynch, blocked the FBI from pursuing criminal charges against Hillary Clinton.
Theepochtimes.com reports: In order for Clinton to be prosecuted, the DOJ required the FBI to establish evidence of intent—even though the gross negligence statute explicitly does not require this.
Because of Comey’s statement, many have mistakenly concluded that the FBI acted independently from DOJ influence in their investigation of Clinton.
And we had multiple conversations, multiple conversations with the Justice Department about charging gross negligence.
FBI Never Looked for Evidence of NegligenceAnderson was asked about her understanding of the difference between gross negligence and extreme carelessness.